-- Taiwan’s CPC Said to Buy Angola Crude From Unipec, Sonangol
-- B y   R u p e r t   R o w l i n g   a n d   S h e r r y   S u
-- 2012-09-20T16:47:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-20/taiwan-s-cpc-said-to-buy-angola-crude-from-unipec-sonangol-1-.html
Taiwan’s CPC Corp. bought three
cargoes of Angolan crude for loading in November from Sonangol
Holdings and China International United Petroleum & Chemical
Corp., known as Unipec, according to two traders who participate
in the market.  CPC purchased one lot each of Palanca for loading on Nov.
14 to Nov. 15 and Cabinda for Nov. 16 to Nov. 17 from Sonangol
as well a consignment of Cabinda from Unipec for Nov. 26 to Nov.
27, the traders said, declining to be identified as the
information is confidential. Each cargo is for one million
barrels.  The company bought 3 million barrels of Angolan Cabinda and
1 million barrels of Palanca crudes for loading in October from
 Chevron Corp. (CVX) , Sonangol Holdings and  Total SA (FP) , according to
three traders with knowledge of the matter.  To contact the reporters on this story:
